# Page Migration — Mandatory Rules

When the user shares a design image (screenshot, Figma export, or mockup) of a page and asks you to build or migrate it, follow these rules strictly. **The image shows WHAT the page should contain — our page layout components define HOW it is structured.**

## 1. The Image Is a Reference, NOT a Blueprint

Design images show the intended content, data, and visual intent. But you must **never replicate the image layout pixel-for-pixel using raw HTML/CSS.** Instead:

1. **Analyze the image** — identify the content zones: navigation, top bar, page header, main content, sidebar, panels, tables, forms, key-value pairs, toolbars, tabs.
2. **Map each zone to a Circuit DS page layout or component** — our page layouts are the guide that must be applied.
3. **The image layout can and will differ from our page layouts** — that is expected. Always prefer our layout components over mimicking the image structure with custom `div`s and flexbox.

## 2. Page Shell — Standard Structure for Every Page

Every page MUST use this standard shell structure:

```html
<div class="flex h-screen overflow-hidden">
  <AppNavigation :menuItems="menuItems" ... />
  <div class="flex-1 flex flex-col min-w-0 overflow-auto">
    <TopBar />
    <PageHeader ... />
    <!-- Page content using a layout component -->
  </div>
</div>
```

| Component | Source | Purpose |
|---|---|---|
| `AppNavigation` | `@jumpcloud/circuit/components` | Left sidebar navigation |
| `TopBar` | `src/components/TopBar.vue` | Top bar with search, icons, AI assistant |
| `PageHeader` | `@jumpcloud/circuit/components` | Page title, subtitle, icon, tabs, actions |

## 3. Page Layout Components — Choose the Right One

After the page shell, the tab/page content MUST use one of our page layout components from `src/components/layout/page-layouts/`. **Never build custom layout structures with raw `div`s when a layout component fits.**

### Available Layouts

| Layout | Path | Use When |
|---|---|---|
| `DetailPageLayout` | `src/components/layout/page-layouts/DetailPageLayout.vue` | Detail/overview pages with panels and an optional sidebar (e.g., device detail highlights, entity overview). Supports `maxWidth` prop and `#sidebar` slot. |
| `ListPageLayout` | `src/components/layout/page-layouts/ListPageLayout.vue` | Full-width list/table pages with an optional sidebar. No max-width constraint. |
| `ConfigPageLayout` | `src/components/layout/page-layouts/ConfigPageLayout.vue` | Configuration/settings pages with form sections and an optional sidebar. Supports `maxWidth` prop and `#sidebar` slot. |
| `DashboardPageLayout` | `src/components/layout/page-layouts/DashboardPageLayout.vue` | Dashboard pages with widgets/cards and an optional sidebar. Supports `maxWidth` prop and `#sidebar` slot. |

### How to Choose

Analyze the image content and match:

- **Main content + right sidebar with key-value info** → `DetailPageLayout` with `#sidebar` slot
- **Full-width table with toolbar** → `ListPageLayout` (no sidebar) or directly in a tab `div`
- **Form sections, settings, toggles** → `ConfigPageLayout`
- **Cards, charts, summary widgets** → `DashboardPageLayout`
- **Tabs where each tab has different layout needs** → Use different layouts per tab content area

### Layout Integration Notes

- All layouts use `w-screen h-screen` by default. When embedding inside a page shell (after AppNavigation + TopBar + PageHeader), override with `class="w-full! h-full!"` so they fit within the existing container.
- All layouts support an optional `#sidebar` slot. If the image shows a right sidebar, use it.
- The default slot is the main content area.

## 4. Content Components — Map Image Elements to Circuit DS

When analyzing the image, map every visual element to the correct Circuit DS component. **Never build custom equivalents.**

**Circuit DS Custom Components** (`import { X } from '@jumpcloud/circuit/components'`):

| Visual Element in Image | Use This Component |
|---|---|
| Card / bordered section with header | `CollapsiblePanel` |
| Collapsible / expandable section | `CollapsiblePanel` with full toggleable pattern (see Section 5) |
| Warning / info / error banner | `MessageNotification` |
| Data table | `DataTable` with `columns` prop |
| Table toolbar (search, filters) | `DataTableToolbar` |
| Checkbox with label | `CheckboxWithLabel` |
| Toggle switch | `ToggleSwitch` |
| Form field with label/validation | `FormField` |
| Dropdown menu | `Dropdown` |
| Radio button with label | `RadioButtonWithLabel` |
| Link text | `LinkText` |
| Styled chip | `Chip` |
| Password input | `Password` |
| Loading spinner | `ProgressSpinner` |
| Toast message | `ToastNotification` |
| OTP input | `InputOtp` |
| Select with custom slots | `SelectWithSlots` |

**Circuit DS Primitive Components** (`import X from 'primevue/x'`) — these ARE Circuit DS components. Circuit owns and styles them via passthrough (PT) configs at `@jumpcloud/circuit/src/primevue-primitives/`. They are imported from `primevue/*` but they are part of Circuit DS:

| Visual Element in Image | Use This Component | Import From |
|---|---|---|
| Button | `Button` | `primevue/button` |
| Tag / badge | `Tag` | `primevue/tag` |
| Segmented control / tab buttons | `SelectButton` | `primevue/selectbutton` |
| Text input | `InputText` | `primevue/inputtext` |
| Dialog / modal | `Dialog` | `primevue/dialog` |
| Textarea | `Textarea` | `primevue/textarea` |
| Dropdown select (no slots) | `Select` | `primevue/select` |
| Skeleton placeholder | `Skeleton` | `primevue/skeleton` |
| Divider line | `Divider` | `primevue/divider` |
| Side drawer | `Drawer` | `primevue/drawer` |
| Popover | `Popover` | `primevue/popover` |
| Context menu | `TieredMenu` | `primevue/tieredmenu` |
| Avatar | `Avatar` | `primevue/avatar` |

**Project-Specific Components** (local to this repo):

| Visual Element in Image | Use This Component | Import From |
|---|---|---|
| Key-value pairs in sidebar | `DetailsKeyValue` | `src/components/DetailsKeyValue.vue` |
| Top bar | `TopBar` | `src/components/TopBar.vue` |

## 5. CollapsiblePanel — Slots and Usage

`CollapsiblePanel` supports several slots for customizing its header and content. Always use these slots instead of building custom card/section structures.

### Full Slot Reference

```html
<CollapsiblePanel
  v-model:collapsed="collapsed"
  toggleable
  header="Section Title"
>
  <template #titleicon="iconProps">
    <FolderIcon :class="iconProps.class" />
  </template>
  <template #actions>
    <Button size="small" label="First Button" variant="outlined" />
    <Button size="small" label="Second Button" variant="outlined" severity="secondary" />
  </template>
  <template #toggleicon="iconProps">
    <ChevronRightIcon :class="iconProps.class" />
  </template>
  <!-- Panel body content -->
</CollapsiblePanel>
```

| Slot | Slot Props | Purpose |
|---|---|---|
| `default` | — | Panel body content |
| `titleicon` | `{ class }` | Icon rendered before the header text |
| `actions` | — | Buttons/links rendered on the right side of the header |
| `toggleicon` | `{ class, collapsed }` | Custom expand/collapse icon |

### Header Action Rules

- **Links** (e.g., "All Groups", "Go to Asset Detail", "Activity Log") must be rendered as `<Button label="..." variant="outlined" severity="secondary" size="small" />` — never as `<a>` tags or plain text links.
- **All header buttons** must use `size="small"` to maintain consistent panel header sizing.

### Simple Example (header + actions only)

```html
<CollapsiblePanel header="Groups (3)">
  <template #actions>
    <Button label="All Groups" variant="outlined" severity="secondary" size="small" />
  </template>
  <!-- panel content -->
</CollapsiblePanel>
```

## 5a. Two-Column Form Layout Inside CollapsiblePanel

When a `CollapsiblePanel` contains form fields, use a **2-column grid with 24px gap** between columns:

```html
<CollapsiblePanel header="User Information">
  <div class="grid grid-cols-2 gap-x-6 gap-y-4">
    <FormField label="First Name">
      <template #default="{ inputId }">
        <InputText :id="inputId" v-model="firstName" class="w-full" />
      </template>
    </FormField>
    <FormField label="Last Name">
      <template #default="{ inputId }">
        <InputText :id="inputId" v-model="lastName" class="w-full" />
      </template>
    </FormField>
    <!-- Full-width field spanning both columns -->
    <FormField label="Description" class="col-span-2">
      <template #default="{ inputId }">
        <Textarea :id="inputId" v-model="description" class="w-full" />
      </template>
    </FormField>
  </div>
</CollapsiblePanel>
```

- Use `gap-x-6` (24px) between columns and `gap-y-4` (16px) between rows.
- Use `col-span-2` for fields that should span the full width.
- Always use `FormField` from Circuit DS to wrap inputs — never bare `<label>` + `<input>` combos.

## 6. Common Mistakes to Avoid

These are real mistakes that have been made. **Never repeat them:**

| Mistake | Correct Approach |
|---|---|
| Using `<div class="border rounded p-4">` as a card | Use `<CollapsiblePanel header="...">` |
| Using PrimeVue `<Panel>` directly | Use `<CollapsiblePanel>` from Circuit |
| Using PrimeVue `<Message>` directly | Use `<MessageNotification>` from Circuit |
| Using PrimeVue `<Checkbox>` directly | Use `<CheckboxWithLabel>` from Circuit |
| Using PrimeVue `<DataTable>` with `<Column>` | Use Circuit's `<DataTable :columns="..." :data="...">` |
| Using PrimeVue `<Toast>` directly | Use `<ToastNotification>` from Circuit |
| Building custom flexbox layouts for main+sidebar | Use a page layout component with `#sidebar` slot |
| Building custom search bars with `<InputText>` + icons | Use `<DataTableToolbar>` for table search |
| Using raw Tailwind `text-2xl`, `bg-white`, `text-gray-500` | Use Circuit tokens: `text-heading-2`, `bg-neutral-surface`, `text-neutral-subtle` |
| Copying the image layout structure with custom `div`s | Map to page layout components — the image is a reference, not a blueprint |
| Using `<a>` tags or text links in `CollapsiblePanel` headers | Use `<Button label="..." variant="outlined" severity="secondary" size="small" />` in `#actions` slot |
| Using `CollapsiblePanel` with only `:toggleable="true"` | Use the full pattern: `v-model:collapsed`, `toggleable`, `#titleicon`, `#toggleicon` slots (see Section 5) |

**CRITICAL — Collapsible panels:** Any time a design image shows an expandable/collapsible section (with a +/- icon, chevron, or expand/collapse toggle), you MUST use the full `CollapsiblePanel` toggleable pattern from Section 5. This means:

1. `v-model:collapsed="someRef"` — bind to a reactive collapsed state
2. `toggleable` — enable toggle behavior
3. `#titleicon` slot — provide a contextual icon before the header text
4. `#toggleicon` slot — use `ChevronRightIcon` with `iconProps.class` for the expand/collapse indicator

Never use the shorthand `:toggleable="true"` alone without the full slot pattern.

## 7. Migration Checklist

Before writing any code for a page migration:

1. **Analyze the image** — list all content zones and visual elements.
2. **Choose the page layout** — pick from `DetailPageLayout`, `ListPageLayout`, `ConfigPageLayout`, or `DashboardPageLayout`.
3. **Map every element to a Circuit DS component** — check `@jumpcloud/circuit/components` exports first, then PrimeVue primitives. Never build custom duplicates.
4. **Set up the page shell** — `AppNavigation` + `TopBar` + `PageHeader` with correct props (icon, title, subtitle, tabs, actions).
5. **Implement tab by tab** — each tab may need a different layout. Choose the best layout component for each.
6. **Verify all imports** — everything must come from Circuit DS (custom or PT-styled primitive). No raw PrimeVue when a Circuit wrapper exists.
7. **Check Figma Code Connect** (if Figma URL provided) — use `get_code_connect_map` and `get_design_context` MCP tools to find the correct component mappings.
